ngland, United Kingdom","Broadbotham, Moterham, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","Broadbotham, Mottram, Cheshire, England":"Mottram, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Woolley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of various places called with Old English <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘wood, clearing’, such as Woolley (Huntingdonshire, Yorkshire), Woolley in Bovey Tracy (Devon), and Woolley in Bradford on Avon (Wiltshire).","Irish (Cavan): in Ireland, according to Woulfe, when this is not the English name, it has been adopted for   Woulfe  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Woulfe","meanings":["English: variant of   Wolf   1 (see also   Wolfe  ). This is the usual spelling of the name in Ireland. An Anglo-Norman family called <i>le Wulf</i> settled in Limerick in the 14th century, their name being Gaelicized as <b>de Bhulbh</b>.","Irish: translation into English of Gaelic <b>Ó Faoláin</b> (see   Whelan  )."]},{"name":"Wooley","meanings":["English: variant of   Woolley  ."]}]},{"name":"Agnes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes Woolley was born in 1370, in England, United Kingdom. She married Robert de Woley in 1394, in Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 4 sons and 2 daughters. She died before 1460, in her hometown."},"et":{"1370–BEF. 1460":"1370–enne 1460","1355–1410":"1355–1410","1395–1461":"1395–1461","1398–Female":"1398–Surnud","1400–Female":"1400–Surnud","1402–Male":"1402–Surnud","1404–Male":"1404–Surnud","1406–Male":"1406–Surnud","1370–1460":"1370–1460","Jan 1395":"jaanuar 1395","1461":"1461","1395":"1395","1394":"1394","1460":"1460","1370":"1370","BEF. 1460":"enne 1460","1404":"1404","about 1406":"umbes 1406","1402":"1402","about 1404":"umbes 1404","1400":"1400","1410":"1410","1355":"1355","about 1402":"umbes 1402","1398":"1398","about 1400":"umbes 1400","about 1398":"umbes 1398","after 1410":"pärast 1410","1406":"1406","Moterham, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Broadbotham, Moterham, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Broadbotham, Mottram, Cheshire, England":"Mottram, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1370–BEF. 1460":"1370–ennen vuotta 1460","1355–1410":"1355–1410","1395–1461":"1395–1461","1398–Female":"1398–Kuollut","1400–Female":"1400–Kuollut","1402–Male":"1402–Kuollut","1404–Male":"1404–Kuollut","1406–Male":"1406–Kuollut","1370–1460":"1370–1460","Jan 1395":"tammikuu 1395","1461":"1461","1395":"1395","1394":"1394","1460":"1460","1370":"1370","BEF. 1460":"ennen vuotta 1460","1404":"1404","about 1406":"noin 1406","1402":"1402","about 1404":"noin 1404","1400":"1400","1410":"1410","1355":"1355","about 1402":"noin 1402","1398":"1398","about 1400":"noin 1400","about 1398":"noin 1398","after 1410":"1410 jälkeen","1406":"1406","Moterham, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Englant